<refentry id="MGR-SETDATANODE">
  <refmeta>
    <refentrytitle>SET DATANODE</refentrytitle>
    <manvolnum>7</manvolnum>
    <refmiscinfo>Manage - Language Statements</refmiscinfo>
  </refmeta>

  <refnamediv>
    <refname>SET DATANODE</refname>
    <refpurpose>change the the value of parameter in the file of postgres.conf which is own to datanode</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

  <indexterm zone="mgr-setdatanode">
    <primary>SET DATANODE</primary>
  </indexterm>

  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <synopsis>
SET DATANODE ALL { parameter = <replaceable class="parameter">value</replaceable> } [, ...] ) [ FORCE ];
SET DATANODE { MASTER | SLAVE | EXTRA } <replaceable class="parameter">nodename</replaceable> { parameter = <replaceable class="parameter">value</replaceable> } [, ...] ) [ FORCE ];
<phrase>where <replaceable class="parameter">Parameter</replaceable> can be one of:</phrase>
    if you add "force" at the tail of the command, it won't check the the value and name of parameter, and it alse won't check the parameter whether exist
	in the file of postgres.conf.
    </synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>

  <refsect1>
    <title>Description</title>

    <para>
      change the the value of parameter in the file of postgres.conf and update PARA table, it won't check the the value and name of parameter correctly if adding 'force' at the tail of command line,in addition,it will update PARA table.
    </para>
  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>
    <title>Parameters</title>

    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>
          <replaceable class="parameter">Parameter</replaceable>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            the parameter that in the file of postgres.conf
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsect1>


  <refsect1>
    <title>Examples</title>

    <para>
      change the the value of 'synchronous_commit' and 'max_wal_senders' in the file of postgres.conf:
      <programlisting>
        set datanode all (synchronous_commit = off, max_wal_senders = 10);
      </programlisting>
    </para>
  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>
    <title>See Also</title>

    <simplelist type="inline">
      <member><xref linkend="mgr-resetdatanode"></member>
    </simplelist>
  </refsect1>


</refentry>
